  "text": "## Firefox CSS calc() Value Overflow Analysis\n\n### Overview\nFirefox crashes when processing CSS calc() expressions with extreme values due to numeric overflow. The issue involves both C++ (Gecko) and Rust (Servo) components that parse and resolve CSS calc() expressions.\n\n### C++ Entry Points (Gecko)\n\n**layout/style/ServoStyleConstsInlines.h** contains the C++ interface for resolving calc values:\n- `StyleCalcLengthPercentage::ResolveToCSSPixels()` (line 726-728): C++ function that calls the Servo FFI binding to resolve calc expressions\n- `StyleCalcLengthPercentage::Resolve()` (line 731-736): Template function that resolves calc values with rounding\n- These functions delegate to the Servo Rust implementation via FFI\n\n### Rust Calc Parsing and Resolution (Servo)\n\n**servo/components/style/values/specified/calc.rs** handles CSS calc() parsing:\n- Defines the `MathFunction` enum for calc(), min(), max(), clamp(), round(), mod(), rem(), and other math functions\n- The `Leaf` enum represents leaf nodes (lengths, percentages, angles, etc.)\n- The `CalcNode` enum represents the abstract syntax tree of calc expressions\n- Parsing logic converts CSS calc() strings into the internal representation\n\n**servo/components/style/values/generics/calc.rs** contains generic calc expression handling:\n- The `CalcNode::resolve_internal()` function (line 928+) recursively evaluates calc expressions\n- Handles arithmetic operations (addition, multiplication, negation) with proper unit tracking\n- Implements min/max/clamp logic with NaN checking\n- The `resolve_map()` function allows transforming leaf values during resolution\n- Critical for evaluating expressions with extreme values that could overflow\n\n**servo/ports/geckolib/glue.rs** provides the FFI binding:\n- `Servo_ResolveCalcLengthPercentage()` (line 9208-9213): Exported C function called from Gecko\n- Resolves the calc expression and returns a f32 pixel value\n- Calls `calc.resolve(computed::Length::new(basis)).px()` which triggers overflow handling\n\n**servo/components/style/values/computed/length_percentage.rs** handles value resolution:\n- `CalcLengthPercentage::resolve()` (line 991-1008): Resolves percentages against basis values\n- Creates `Length::new(self.clamping_mode.clamp(px.px())).normalized()` which applies clamping and normalization\n- Converts calculated percentages to absolute lengths\n\n**servo/components/style/values/computed/length.rs** implements overflow handling:\n- `CSSPixelLength::normalized()` (line 237-239): Converts NaN to 0.0 using the `normalize()` function\n- `CSSPixelLength::finite()` (line 243-245): **PRIMARY OVERFLOW HANDLER** - clamps values to f32::MIN and f32::MAX after normalization\n- These functions prevent infinity and extreme values from propagating through the layout engine\n\n### Numeric Overflow Handling Chain\n\nThe call chain from C++ to overflow handling:\n1. C++ calls `StyleCalcLengthPercentage::ResolveToCSSPixels()`\n2. Which calls FFI binding `Servo_ResolveCalcLengthPercentage()`\n3. Which calls `CalcLengthPercentage::resolve()`\n4. Which evaluates the calc expression using `resolve_internal()`\n5. Creates a `Length::new()` with clamped and normalized values\n6. The `CSSPixelLength::finite()` function clamps extreme values to f32::MIN/MAX\n\n### Root Cause of Crash\n\nThe crash likely occurs when:\n- CSS calc() expressions contain extreme arithmetic values (e.g., `calc(999999999999px + 999999999999px)`)\n- The arithmetic operations in `resolve_internal()` produce infinity or values exceeding float bounds\n- These extreme values are not properly clamped before being used in layout calculations\n- The `finite()` function provides the safety mechanism but may not be called in all code paths\n\n### Key Files Summary\n\n- **Parsing**: servo/components/style/values/specified/calc.rs\n- **Generic Evaluation**: servo/components/style/values/generics/calc.rs  \n- **Overflow Safety**: servo/components/style/values/computed/length.rs (finite() function)\n- **Value Resolution**: servo/components/style/values/computed/length_percentage.rs\n- **FFI Binding**: servo/ports/geckolib/glue.rs\n- **C++ Interface**: layout/style/ServoStyleConstsInlines.h\n"
}

